blog.name: phandomreversebang
blog.title: Phandom Reverse Bang 2019
blog.description:
Welcome to the 4th edition of the Phandom Reverse Bang! We're a big bang in reverse; artists create themed pieces of art, and authors claim said work to write a fic based around them! 
  Mobile Navigation

summary: Hello and Welcome to the Phandom Reverse Bang 2019!  If you don’t know what the Phandom Reverse Bang is, here is a synopsis: ...
caption:
Hello and Welcome to the Phandom Reverse Bang 2019!

If you don’t know what the Phandom Reverse Bang is, here is a synopsis: 

  • It’s the Phandom Big Bang, but in reverse! If you don’t know what the PBB is, the Phandom Big Bang is another event that’s held where the author submits a fic idea that they’re going to work on, and a beta and artist claim the fic so the that author can bring it to life! For the Phandom Reverse Bang, or the PRB, it’s the artist that is in charge! The artists will submit an art prompt and some art to be written about by an author and it’s the author and beta’s job to flow the art into words and provide a nice fic for the artist!

This is this years tentative schedule:

  • Artist Sign Ups - April 6th - 13th
  • Author/Beta Sign Ups - April 14th - 21st
  • Artist drafts Due- April 21st
  • Claiming for Authors for art and Betas- April 26th - April 28th
  • Team Reveal- May 1st
  • Mandatory Check In’s Sent Out- May 19th
  • Posting- June 15th to July 1st (or so)

Artist sign ups for the 2019 Phandom Reverse Bang are officially open!

Just like before we are not limiting art to just drawings, any sort of art is welcome. If you wish to collab on an art piece that is accepted as well.

Please Keep in Mind:

  • You can only sign up for three roles. That can be a combination of an artist, author and/or beta. So, you can’t sign up to do 3 pieces of art and be an author/beta as well.
  • For the posting days you must have one completed piece of art. Just like last time we are allowing more than just traditional/digital art. Artistic gif sets, moodboards, drawings/graphic designs all count as art. If you are unsure if what you want to do is considered “art” just send an ask and we can let you know! You will need to have an art draft done and submitted to us by April 21st for claiming!
  • Please make sure that your messages (asks at the minimum) are turned on so we have a way to contact you if needed and your team does too when the time comes.

For additional details click here (and if your question still isn’t answered, send us an ask!)

**** LINK TO ARTIST SIGN UPS ****
